06:22.257 --> 06:25.092
(LAUGHS) Now, David,
come on, man.
Are you kidding?

06:25.385 --> 06:27.303
Hey, she's a grandmother.

06:27.387 --> 06:29.680
Well, so when did
that ever stop you?

06:33.060 --> 06:34.226
(EXCLAIMING)

06:43.987 --> 06:46.113
Hey, man. You better
get a move on. I already
played your theme.

06:46.198 --> 06:48.741
Yeah, I heard it.
You're a real human being.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.951
And you're
on the air, baby.

06:52.079 --> 06:53.579
All right.

07:04.382 --> 07:06.717
"Men have destroyed
the roads of wonder

07:06.843 --> 07:09.637
"And their cities
squat like black toads

07:09.721 --> 07:12.348
"In the orchards of life
nothing is clean or real

07:12.432 --> 07:16.143
"Or as a girl,
naked to love
or be a man with"

07:17.354 --> 07:19.605
This is Dave Garver
with a little verse,
a little talk

07:19.689 --> 07:23.734
and five hours of music
to be very, very nice
to each other by.

07:31.535 --> 07:33.536
KRML, Dave Garver speaking.

07:33.620 --> 07:34.870
WOMAN: Hello?

07:34.955 --> 07:36.288
Hi, what'll it be?

07:36.373 --> 07:38.040
Play Misty for me.

07:38.125 --> 07:39.291
Misty, huh?

07:40.252 --> 07:43.838
We have that
right on the play rack.
Thanks for calling.

07:45.006 --> 07:48.884
I see you got your little
Misty chick calling you again.
All righty.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.679
Swing low.
You take it easy now, huh?

07:52.722 --> 07:54.181
See you in the a.m.

07:58.728 --> 08:00.563
KRML, Dave Garver.

08:30.635 --> 08:31.844
Hi, Murphy.

08:31.928 --> 08:34.013
Oh. Hi, Dave.
No messages for you.

08:34.097 --> 08:35.139
No?

08:35.222 --> 08:36.515
Heard your show tonight.

08:36.600 --> 08:37.683
Yeah?

08:37.767 --> 08:40.311
Well, it sure beats hell
out of working for a living.

08:40.395 --> 08:42.062
Thanks for the plug.

08:42.147 --> 08:43.438
What are friends for?

08:43.523 --> 08:44.899
Bartender.

08:44.983 --> 08:46.901
Coke? Coming right up.

08:50.322 --> 08:52.531
Uh-uh.

08:52.616 --> 08:55.284
She's waiting for someone.

08:55.493 --> 08:56.535
You sure?

08:56.620 --> 08:59.455
That's what she says.
Guys have been
striking out all night.

09:05.378 --> 09:06.462
One game?

09:07.631 --> 09:08.839
Cry Bastion?

09:09.132 --> 09:10.257
What else?

09:10.342 --> 09:13.928
Okay, coach.
You asked for it.

09:17.641 --> 09:20.142
Don't take all night. Move.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.310
Okay.

09:28.944 --> 09:30.027
Move.

09:32.197 --> 09:33.822
Palfrey's Gambit.

09:34.699 --> 09:36.158
Dirty rat.

09:36.243 --> 09:37.910
Are we playing
Copenhagen rules?

09:37.994 --> 09:40.246
Make it easy on
yourself, Murph.

09:46.836 --> 09:48.254
Cry Bastion.

09:49.464 --> 09:51.340
Sorry, no Bastion.

09:51.424 --> 09:53.342
Damn, I didn't see that.

09:53.510 --> 09:55.970
It's too bad,
Murphy. Too bad.

10:04.854 --> 10:06.272
Careful now.

10:06.356 --> 10:08.190
That ought to do it.

10:10.735 --> 10:12.611
Be really careful now.

10:14.614 --> 10:15.864
Careful.

10:18.034 --> 10:19.034
Hi.

10:20.578 --> 10:22.079
He doesn't see it.

10:22.163 --> 10:24.081
Oh, yeah?

10:24.165 --> 10:25.541
Cry Bastion.

10:29.379 --> 10:32.047
Fool's ploy, my man.
Fool's ploy.

10:34.217 --> 10:36.260
Care to play the winner?

10:36.344 --> 10:38.512
I'll just watch.

10:38.596 --> 10:40.681
My name is Dave Garver.

10:40.765 --> 10:41.890
Evelyn Draper.

10:43.018 --> 10:44.977
Sit down, Evelyn Draper?

10:46.187 --> 10:48.897
Care for a drink?
Okay.

10:49.024 --> 10:51.025
What'll it be?
Surprise me.

10:51.109 --> 10:52.276
Screwdriver.

10:52.360 --> 10:54.069
Nice game. Congratulations.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.237
Thank you.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.780
What happened?

10:56.865 --> 10:58.657
I won.

10:58.742 --> 11:00.159
How? When?

11:01.745 --> 11:03.370
When you said, "Okay."

11:05.874 --> 11:07.374
I ought to be mad.

11:07.459 --> 11:09.001
But you're not.

11:09.919 --> 11:11.295
Not really.

11:19.471 --> 11:22.806
Well, it certainly
was nice of you to bring
me home, Mr...

11:22.891 --> 11:24.224
Garver?

11:24.309 --> 11:25.726
That's right.

11:25.810 --> 11:30.773
I don't think I've been
stood up on a date since the
ninth grade back in Albany.

11:32.776 --> 11:34.651
Is something wrong?

11:34.736 --> 11:38.280
No. I keep getting the feeling
I know you from someplace.

11:39.115 --> 11:40.115
You do?

11:42.243 --> 11:44.203
Here. Why don't
you let me do that?

11:44.287 --> 11:46.538
Oh, no, no.
That's all right.
I've got it.

11:46.623 --> 11:48.415
Why don't you see
if you can get
the fire started?

11:57.342 --> 11:59.676
There are some matches
right next to it.

11:59.761 --> 12:01.095
All right.

12:08.436 --> 12:11.772
It's getting late.
You're sure I'm not
keeping you up?

12:11.856 --> 12:14.650
No. I rarely get to bed
before 3:00 a.m.

12:17.779 --> 12:19.988
I didn't have
a date tonight.

12:21.157 --> 12:25.411
I went there because
you talk about it on
your program sometimes.

12:25.495 --> 12:27.287
And I wanted to meet you.

12:33.628 --> 12:35.838
I listen to you
all the time.

12:36.923 --> 12:38.549
I knew somebody
was out there.

12:38.633 --> 12:40.676
(LAUGHS) You're
making fun of me.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.970
No, I'm not.

12:43.054 --> 12:44.680
Say something else, huh?

12:45.014 --> 12:46.223
Such as?

12:47.016 --> 12:48.934
"Play Misty for me"?

12:49.018 --> 12:50.352
Very good.

12:53.857 --> 12:56.316
You sure I'm not
keeping you up?

12:56.401 --> 12:57.818
Don't you like me?

12:59.737 --> 13:02.114
You're a very nice girl.

13:02.198 --> 13:05.117
But who needs nice girls?

13:05.201 --> 13:08.370
No, I like them.

13:08.455 --> 13:10.914
I'm kind of hung up on one.

13:10.999 --> 13:12.583
And you don't want
to complicate your life.

13:12.667 --> 13:13.959
That's exactly right.

13:14.043 --> 13:15.794
Well, neither do I.

13:15.879 --> 13:19.923
But that's no reason
we shouldn't sleep together
tonight, if we feel like it.

13:57.795 --> 13:59.087
(DOOR CLOSING)

14:29.285 --> 14:30.786
(TYPEWRITER CLACKING)

14:33.998 --> 14:35.749
Solid silicone.

14:35.833 --> 14:39.545
Hi, ho, David, my man!
How you been, baby?

14:39.629 --> 14:42.673
See you got the joint
cleaned up for once.
The Heavy digs it.

14:42.757 --> 14:43.882
Care for a beer?

14:43.967 --> 14:46.385
No, not really. I could go
for something more uplifting,

14:46.469 --> 14:48.887
but not a brew, David.
Not a brew, my man.

14:48.972 --> 14:51.890
Beer is all we've got.
Hey, Al, you're gonna
have to ease on out.

14:51.975 --> 14:53.600
I got a heck of a lot
of work to do today.

14:53.685 --> 14:56.061
Yeah, but you don't
understand, man. I've been
sent over here to get you.

14:56.145 --> 14:57.312
By whom?

14:57.397 --> 14:59.648
That old chick I go with.
What's her name?

14:59.732 --> 15:01.400
Carol?
Yeah, that's the one.

15:01.484 --> 15:02.985
Girl thinks you've been
working too hard, man.

15:03.069 --> 15:04.528
She said we
should get together
and go out tonight.

15:04.612 --> 15:06.113
Blast the town open
a little taste.

15:06.573 --> 15:07.739
Who's this "we"?

15:07.824 --> 15:10.826
Me, you, her and one of them
hens that you can dig up.

15:11.327 --> 15:15.080
Man, there is a fantastic
new Mexican place in
Carmel called Susinos.

15:15.164 --> 15:18.250
And the albondigas soup
is not to be believed.
It is a mind-bender...

15:18.334 --> 15:22.004
I know the joint,
but I don't have a date,
and I got a lot to do, really.

15:22.088 --> 15:24.089
Big deal, man. Get one!

15:24.841 --> 15:29.011
Look. If you have any problems
getting one, I'll get one
for you, as nice as I look.

15:29.178 --> 15:32.097
It's too late, and besides,
I've got a lot of work to do.

15:32.181 --> 15:33.682
Hey, man, but you
gotta eat, David.

15:33.766 --> 15:36.226
Yes, well, I'm gonna
whip up something right
here in my own kitchen.

15:36.311 --> 15:39.646
You know, David,
I'm really worried
about your social life.

15:39.731 --> 15:41.982
You know something,
you're gonna make somebody
a tremendous mother.

15:42.066 --> 15:44.067
Too narrow in the pelvis.

15:44.694 --> 15:49.114
I sure appreciate you
dropping by, Al. Come by
again sometime, anytime.

15:49.198 --> 15:52.075
Never let it be said
that Sweet Al Monte
can't take a hint.

15:52.160 --> 15:53.785
Who's hinting?
Hi.

15:53.870 --> 15:55.871
Why, hi there, yourself.

15:56.664 --> 15:58.498
Dave Garver live here?

15:58.583 --> 16:01.084
Well, that depends
on your point of view.

16:01.544 --> 16:02.794
Oh, hi.

16:02.879 --> 16:04.713
This stuff weighs a ton.
Where's the kitchen?

16:04.797 --> 16:07.132
Right inside.
Just come on in
and help yourself.

16:07.216 --> 16:09.718
Swing right around
the bend there.
Thank you.

16:11.679 --> 16:14.264
I know, David, she's
from Chicken Delight.

16:14.349 --> 16:16.642
Look, don't work
too hard, my man.

16:16.726 --> 16:18.310
Don't strain yourself.

16:23.399 --> 16:25.192
How come you
don't have any beer?

16:25.276 --> 16:27.361
And what is this?
A shrunken head?

16:27.445 --> 16:28.987
Who was that guy?
Does he live here?

16:29.072 --> 16:30.739
Hey, look. I wanted...
I hope you like steak.

16:30.865 --> 16:33.158
I thought you look like
a steak-and-potatoes type.
Hang on.

16:33.242 --> 16:36.745
I said to myself,
a nice green salad with
Roquefort and tomatoes,

16:36.829 --> 16:38.455
and baked potato with...

16:38.539 --> 16:40.082
What's going on here?

16:40.750 --> 16:41.917
Don't send me away.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.418
No, I want to
ask you a question.

16:43.503 --> 16:45.420
I just wanted to surprise you.

16:46.047 --> 16:47.297
Surprise?

16:47.924 --> 16:50.634
What happens if he and I
had been talking business?

16:50.718 --> 16:52.719
Or maybe I have female
company or something,

16:52.804 --> 16:54.721
and you come traipsing in
with an armload of groceries?

16:54.806 --> 16:56.932
That would be some surprise.

16:57.934 --> 16:59.267
I'm sorry.

16:59.811 --> 17:02.104
Why don't you keep that stuff?
I think I've lost my appetite.

17:02.188 --> 17:03.855
Hang on a minute.

17:03.940 --> 17:05.773
I'm just trying to
tell you something,
that's all.

17:05.858 --> 17:08.026
I don't understand.
Should I go or should I stay?
What do you want?

17:08.111 --> 17:11.530
I'm trying to tell you
that there's a telephone, and
I pick it up and I dial it.

17:11.614 --> 17:14.700
You answer and I say,
"Hey, what are you doing?"

17:14.784 --> 17:16.660
And I say,
"I'll be right over."

17:16.743 --> 17:19.371
Fine. Next time,
why don't we do it that way?

17:20.540 --> 17:23.290
Okay. Any way you like.
Next time.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.169
How do you like your steak?

17:27.463 --> 17:28.964
Extremely rare.

17:29.424 --> 17:32.300
That's just how I like mine.
Extremely rare.

17:34.429 --> 17:36.972
I'll get some wine.
Here. A little vino.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.974
Vino! All this
and heaven, too!

17:39.100 --> 17:41.977
Wow! Terrific!

17:43.730 --> 17:45.814
This is gonna be some dinner.

17:45.940 --> 17:49.192
Hey, what happened
to that discussion
we had last time?

17:49.569 --> 17:52.320
You know, the deal
about no strings and all that?

17:53.448 --> 17:55.991
There are no strings,
but I never said anything

17:56.075 --> 17:58.994
about not coming back
for seconds, did I?

18:00.788 --> 18:02.831
That's right. You didn't.

18:11.758 --> 18:12.924
When will I see you?

18:13.009 --> 18:14.843
I'll give you a call.

18:15.344 --> 18:17.179
(LAUGHS) Dave, you're funny.

18:17.972 --> 18:19.347
How's that?

18:19.515 --> 18:22.476
If you want to keep playing
these games, okay,

18:22.560 --> 18:24.770
but they're really
not necessary anymore,
not for me.

18:24.854 --> 18:27.689
Hey! People trying
to sleep here!

18:28.316 --> 18:30.609
People are trying
to talk here!

18:30.735 --> 18:32.360
How'd you like to
tell it to the law?

18:32.445 --> 18:34.404
How'd you like
to go screw yourself?

18:34.489 --> 18:36.406
(HONKING)

18:36.491 --> 18:39.868
Hey! Take it easy!
Guy's just trying
to sleep, that's all.

18:43.539 --> 18:44.539
You're right.

18:44.624 --> 18:47.375
It's a terrific morning.
Why be selfish with it?

18:49.921 --> 18:51.171
Bye-bye.

20:15.381 --> 20:16.882
Hey, wait a minute!

20:17.717 --> 20:18.800
Yeah?

20:19.427 --> 20:20.427
Oh.

20:20.678 --> 20:23.805
Excuse me, I saw
the sweater, and I thought
you were somebody else.

20:23.890 --> 20:25.557
Oh, you must be David.

20:40.323 --> 20:43.158
Where have you been?

20:46.662 --> 20:48.914
Oh, around.

20:50.833 --> 20:54.419
I was trying to join
the revolt against
the representational.

20:54.503 --> 20:55.921
Didn't quite
make that, though.

20:56.005 --> 20:58.715
So now I'm just
trying to play it cool.

21:00.176 --> 21:01.801
Not quite making that, either.

21:01.886 --> 21:03.678
Got time for a break?

21:05.097 --> 21:07.515
Yeah.
Let's go.

21:13.606 --> 21:14.940
When did you get in town?

21:15.024 --> 21:16.274
Yesterday.

21:16.359 --> 21:17.776
You weren't
gonna call me?

21:17.860 --> 21:20.111
Of course I was.
I had to get settled first.

21:20.196 --> 21:23.406
Well, you shouldn't
lend your sweaters
to blabbermouths.

21:24.241 --> 21:25.784
You've gotten thinner.

21:25.868 --> 21:27.285
Oh, no!

21:28.371 --> 21:31.164
Well, so much for Sausalito.

21:31.874 --> 21:35.543
Sausalito?
That's where I was staying.
Jay Jay's place.

21:36.337 --> 21:37.629
Jay Jay's place?

21:37.713 --> 21:38.755
Oh, it's nothing much, really.

21:38.839 --> 21:41.675
It's just a little
pied-Ã -terre, but it's
handy to the fleet.

21:41.759 --> 21:43.677
You told me you didn't
know where she was.

21:43.761 --> 21:45.679
So I lied. Picket me.

21:46.555 --> 21:47.722
Thanks a lot.

21:47.807 --> 21:49.891
Listen, stud,
it wasn't my idea.

21:49.976 --> 21:51.643
You should have
caught her act.

21:51.727 --> 21:54.813
The whole Bette Davis,
through-finished-kaput scene.

21:54.897 --> 21:56.106
And at 3:00 a.m.

21:56.190 --> 21:59.567
Come on, Jay Jay.
He's exaggerating.

22:01.070 --> 22:04.489
Well, I'll check with Malcolm.
Maybe I can get you
the afternoon off.

22:06.283 --> 22:08.243
What happened, pussycat?

22:08.744 --> 22:10.954
He ran into Anjelica.
She told him I was back.

22:11.038 --> 22:14.958
That bitch should be hung
by the thumbs or something
equally appropriate.

22:15.084 --> 22:17.002
DAVE: It's all set up.

22:17.086 --> 22:18.420
Let's go.

22:18.546 --> 22:20.463
Oh, well, it's nothing
personal, really.

22:20.548 --> 22:22.966
It's just that I happen
to think she could be
a first-rate artist

22:23.050 --> 22:25.760
if her damned hormones
didn't keep getting
in the way.

22:25.845 --> 22:27.595
There's not much
he can do about that.

22:27.680 --> 22:29.264
He could kill himself.

22:29.890 --> 22:32.892
Jay Jay, why don't you
go cruise some sailors, huh?

22:33.436 --> 22:36.438
Oh, please, don't
mention seafood.

22:37.898 --> 22:38.857
(LAUGHS)

22:38.941 --> 22:40.191
Come on.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.703
I really missed
this place.

22:51.787 --> 22:53.246
I missed you.

22:54.290 --> 22:57.542
You'd do me a big favor
if you didn't say things
like that.

22:57.835 --> 22:59.252
Why is that?

23:00.046 --> 23:02.964
I don't know.
Somehow it brings out
the worst in me.

23:03.132 --> 23:06.968
It makes me want
to say things like,
"How's that redhead?"

23:07.053 --> 23:08.136
What?

23:08.262 --> 23:11.389
The redhead,
the one who worked
in the bookstore.

23:11.474 --> 23:13.767
She went back to
Berkeley or whatever.

23:13.851 --> 23:15.393
Oh, that's too bad.

23:16.103 --> 23:19.856
You always have that
blonde from Santa Barbara
to fall back on.

23:20.399 --> 23:24.277
If that's the phrase
I'm looking for, and
I think it probably is.

23:25.321 --> 23:28.782
What are we gonna do?
Go through a whole list?
Is that it?

23:28.866 --> 23:30.700
Who's got that kind of time?

23:31.702 --> 23:34.287
I just don't know if
I'm up to it anymore.

23:34.371 --> 23:35.747
Up to what?

23:36.791 --> 23:41.086
Those nights sitting and
waiting for you to finish
your program and come by.

23:41.170 --> 23:43.588
Nights when it would
start to get late

23:43.672 --> 23:46.424
and I'd start to think,

23:46.509 --> 23:51.096
"I wonder if he's run himself
off a cliff. Or maybe
he's run into a blonde."

23:52.139 --> 23:55.141
There was a time when
I started rooting for
the accident, you know.

23:55.226 --> 23:58.394
I mean, if it was a choice
between that and a blonde.

23:58.479 --> 24:00.855
You know how secure
you make me feel.

24:00.940 --> 24:03.066
Oh, I didn't wish you
anything too serious.

24:03.150 --> 24:06.277
Just a couple of
months in traction.

24:06.362 --> 24:08.029
You're all heart.

24:08.489 --> 24:12.992
You know, the thing I hate
the most in the whole world
is a jealous female,

24:13.077 --> 24:15.620
and that's what
I was getting to be.

24:15.704 --> 24:17.956
TOBIE: That's why
I had to split.

24:18.040 --> 24:23.294
I was starting to
be one of my most
unfavorite people.

24:23.379 --> 24:26.381
I hated it.
I know you did, too.

24:31.512 --> 24:34.055
That still works, anyway.

24:34.140 --> 24:36.182
Too well, sometimes.

24:36.267 --> 24:37.809
What does that mean?

24:37.893 --> 24:41.646
I mean, there's a little spot
in the middle of each day,
just about your size.

24:43.482 --> 24:46.985
Well, there's lots of
girls my size, if you're
really looking.

24:47.069 --> 24:50.071
I'm not. That's what
I'm trying to tell you.

24:53.659 --> 24:55.660
You mean you've
given up girls?

24:55.744 --> 24:59.664
I haven't exactly been
the monk of the month
or anything like that,

24:59.748 --> 25:02.292
but I have been
making an effort.

25:03.335 --> 25:06.129
Boy, there must be
a real consternation
among those gropies.

25:06.213 --> 25:07.672
That's "groupies," isn't it?

25:07.756 --> 25:10.341
I don't know.
Groupies, gropies.

25:12.011 --> 25:15.346
You know, you've
got to be fair.
It hasn't just been my fault.

25:15.431 --> 25:18.266
Listen, I know.
They kept overpowering you.

25:20.102 --> 25:22.395
DAVE: You get a little bit
of the blame, too, you know.

25:22.479 --> 25:26.482
You and that parade of
roommates that keep moving
in and out of your place.

25:26.567 --> 25:29.068
I didn't realize they
were such a trial to you.

25:29.153 --> 25:31.196
What trial? I enjoyed it.

25:31.822 --> 25:34.908
You and I sitting
in front of the fireplace,

25:35.075 --> 25:39.787
and then some chick sitting
there with a bathrobe on,
eating Fig Newtons.

25:39.872 --> 25:41.497
(LAUGHS)

25:41.582 --> 25:43.541
DAVE: What about the one
with the St. Bernard?

25:43.626 --> 25:46.127
She was a real winner.
She took up enough space.

25:46.212 --> 25:49.297
And then that other one,
the one that took
the flute lessons.

25:49.381 --> 25:52.175
Yeah, well maybe it was
a little rough on you.

25:57.556 --> 26:01.184
I can think of
a thousand reasons why
we should try again.

26:09.860 --> 26:12.695
(SIGHS) I've got about
seven million things to do.

26:13.864 --> 26:15.782
What do you think?
You want to try
for a new start,

26:15.866 --> 26:17.283
right from the letter "A"?

26:22.831 --> 26:24.582
What am I gonna do with you?

26:24.667 --> 26:25.833
A lot.

26:29.672 --> 26:32.423
Oh, hi. Excuse me.

26:32.508 --> 26:33.549
Hi.

26:35.094 --> 26:37.178
You've met Anjelica, my...

26:37.304 --> 26:39.097
Roommate. Yes.

26:39.181 --> 26:43.518
I think I'll drive into
Carmel and see if I can't
find some cleaning solvent.

26:43.602 --> 26:45.770
There's plenty under the sink.

26:45.854 --> 26:47.897
Okay.

26:47.982 --> 26:50.483
This house ought to
have a revolving door.

26:50.693 --> 26:54.112
You know when my father
left me this house,
he left me payments.

26:54.196 --> 26:55.947
I can't handle that
expense by myself,

26:56.031 --> 26:58.283
and most girls
find the isolation
is too much for them.

26:58.367 --> 26:59.951
It's a long way from town.

27:00.035 --> 27:01.035
I know.

27:01.954 --> 27:03.997
I better get back to work.

27:07.001 --> 27:08.293
Thanks.

27:08.377 --> 27:10.169
That's it, "Thanks"?

27:14.216 --> 27:16.926
Four months in Sausalito
is a long time.

27:17.720 --> 27:21.556
I am not gonna
get back on that same
old merry-go-round again.

27:21.640 --> 27:24.684
What do I have to do,
give you a notarized
statement?

27:26.812 --> 27:30.273
I need a couple of
more days to try and

27:30.357 --> 27:32.317
figure out where I'm at.

27:33.569 --> 27:37.989
Okay. You get your bearings,
and then you'll give me
a call, all right?

27:44.997 --> 27:46.331
(SIGHING)

27:46.749 --> 27:48.708
(PHONE RINGING)

27:51.086 --> 27:52.170
Hi, Murph.

27:52.254 --> 27:53.421
Oh, hi, Dave.

27:54.423 --> 27:56.049
Sardine Factory.

27:57.926 --> 27:59.344
Dave Garver?

28:00.596 --> 28:02.764
You said this is Evelyn?

28:03.098 --> 28:04.265
No.

28:04.350 --> 28:06.601
Sorry, you've just missed him.

28:08.896 --> 28:10.063
What do you mean?

28:10.147 --> 28:12.190
He's gone.
He's not here.

28:13.233 --> 28:15.234
I think you'd
better look again.

28:15.319 --> 28:16.903
Believe me,
you just missed him.

28:16.987 --> 28:19.655
Now, if you're interested
in someone a little more
suave and sophisticated,

28:19.782 --> 28:21.949
(HANGS UP PHONE)
I'll be happy to...

28:22.201 --> 28:24.535
That's what I get for
being a dirty old man.

28:24.620 --> 28:28.373
There's a message for you,
a Madge somebody
from San Francisco.

28:28.457 --> 28:29.707
Brenner?
Yeah, that's it.

28:29.792 --> 28:31.667
Al Monte gave her
this number.

28:31.752 --> 28:33.920
"Received pictures
and biography.

28:34.004 --> 28:37.173
"Please send a two-hour
tape of your show
as soon as possible."

28:37.257 --> 28:38.424
Hey, thanks, Murph.

28:38.509 --> 28:39.550
Don't mention it.

28:39.635 --> 28:43.012
I can't tell you
how thrilled I am to be
your social secretary.

28:45.391 --> 28:47.266
You will put that on my tab?

29:07.663 --> 29:08.663
Surprise!

29:15.003 --> 29:16.129
What are you doing here?

29:16.213 --> 29:18.381
It was funny. I was
calling you from that
phone booth over there,

29:18.465 --> 29:20.758
and he was telling me
you'd left, and I was
staring right at your car.

29:20.843 --> 29:22.468
(GIGGLING)
Isn't that funny?

29:23.720 --> 29:25.513
Yeah, kind of funny.

29:26.807 --> 29:28.349
Why didn't you take my call?

29:28.434 --> 29:30.435
Where does it say that
I gotta drop what I'm doing

29:30.519 --> 29:32.770
and answer the phone
every time it rings?

29:33.272 --> 29:37.108
Do you know your nostrils
flare out into little wings
when you're mad?

29:37.484 --> 29:38.484
It's kind of cute.

29:38.569 --> 29:39.944
Come on, Evelyn.
I gotta go.

29:40.028 --> 29:41.028
I'd love a Coke.

29:41.113 --> 29:42.947
Not tonight. I gotta
get to the station.

29:43.031 --> 29:44.407
No, you don't.

29:44.491 --> 29:48.035
Hey, you're talking
to your number one fan.
You don't work tonight.

29:48.745 --> 29:49.745
(SIGHS)

29:49.830 --> 29:51.372
I've got this show
that I'm trying to set,

29:51.457 --> 29:53.291
and it happens to be
a very important show to me.

29:53.375 --> 29:56.169
That means I gotta pick
the music, I got to
write the lead-ins

29:56.253 --> 29:58.463
and I gotta find
some poetry.
Now come on, will you?

29:58.547 --> 29:59.755
Poetry?

29:59.840 --> 30:01.549
Let me help you.
I'm terrific with poetry.

30:01.633 --> 30:03.050
I know all kinds by heart.
Not tonight!

30:12.269 --> 30:14.145
Does he want his keys?

30:14.229 --> 30:15.188
Come on, Evelyn.

30:15.272 --> 30:17.148
Speak. Come on!

30:17.232 --> 30:18.774
God!

30:18.859 --> 30:21.360
Good boy!
Let's hear it.
Come on.

30:22.362 --> 30:24.071
Come on.
Give me my keys.

30:24.865 --> 30:26.407
Come on. Give me the keys.
Come on.

30:26.492 --> 30:28.951
(LAUGHING)

30:29.036 --> 30:31.454
Give me the keys,
God damn it!

30:32.372 --> 30:34.207
MAN 1: Having some
trouble, lady?

30:34.291 --> 30:35.416
Get lost!

30:35.501 --> 30:37.502
Yeah, get lost, assholes!

30:38.253 --> 30:40.004
MAN 2: Yeah, let's split.
He's got enough
trouble already.

30:40.088 --> 30:41.756
MAN 1: Yeah. Excuse me.

30:47.429 --> 30:49.472
Bye. See you later.

31:37.771 --> 31:40.147
EVELYN: Hi. Get all
your work done?

31:47.406 --> 31:48.864
What do you want, Evelyn?

31:49.408 --> 31:50.449
One Coke?

31:51.159 --> 31:53.661
I'll tell you, tonight
I'm really whipped.

31:56.790 --> 31:58.165
(GIGGLES)

32:48.008 --> 32:49.258
What time is it?

32:49.718 --> 32:51.135
Time for me to go home.

32:52.763 --> 32:54.388
Go back to sleep.

32:56.725 --> 32:58.643
Hey, I've got an idea.

32:58.727 --> 33:00.186
What's that?

33:00.270 --> 33:02.605
Some night this week,
after the show,

33:02.689 --> 33:05.816
corned beef and potato salad,
dill pickles, the whole bit.

33:05.901 --> 33:07.860
My place. Deal?

33:07.944 --> 33:09.445
I'll call you.

33:16.828 --> 33:18.746
Thursday's good for me.

33:30.926 --> 33:32.176
(DOOR CLOSING)

33:46.942 --> 33:49.151
Oh, shit.

34:29.650 --> 34:34.112
And now from KRML,
the big-band sounds
of Dee Barton.

34:34.197 --> 34:36.114
Here's a fresh reel of
tape for your air check.

34:36.199 --> 34:37.742
You want me
to thread it up?

34:37.826 --> 34:39.994
No, leave it here. Thanks.

34:40.078 --> 34:42.913
All right. I think I will
go out and hit the streets,
but before doing that,

34:42.998 --> 34:46.125
I will blow me
a little number. Would you
care to partake, my man?

34:46.208 --> 34:48.168
Take it in the other room,
will you?

34:48.295 --> 34:51.045
I get zonked just
breathing the air around here.

34:51.130 --> 34:53.215
All right, be that way.

34:54.676 --> 34:55.885
Al?

34:55.969 --> 34:57.052
Yeah?

35:01.725 --> 35:04.101
Do you ever find yourself

35:04.186 --> 35:06.812
being completely
smothered by somebody?

35:06.897 --> 35:08.105
Anybody I know?

35:08.190 --> 35:10.274
Yeah, you met her
at my house the other day.

35:10.358 --> 35:12.568
Ooh! Chicken Delight!

35:12.652 --> 35:14.862
Well, that's what I call
a pretty good smothering,
cousin.

35:14.946 --> 35:19.366
You start a relationship
thinking you're gonna be
completely honest,

35:19.451 --> 35:22.578
and all of a sudden
the whole thing
gets out of hand.

35:22.662 --> 35:24.288
Yeah, well, what's
the problem?

35:24.372 --> 35:27.416
The problem is
I've been trying to
un-complicate my life,

35:27.501 --> 35:30.085
and now I can't even
answer the doorbell.

35:30.170 --> 35:32.630
Besides, Tobie's back.

35:32.714 --> 35:34.548
Oh, really? Tobie? When?

35:34.674 --> 35:36.008
I ran into her Sunday.

35:36.092 --> 35:38.385
That was a goody.

35:38.470 --> 35:39.929
Hey, I'll tell you
the truth, David.

35:40.013 --> 35:43.849
I've always thought that
Tobie was one of the foxiest
chicks on the peninsula.

35:43.934 --> 35:46.644
And why you gotta have
so much action, I just
don't understand it, anyway.

35:46.728 --> 35:47.978
You know what I mean?

35:48.063 --> 35:51.148
It's just a hang-up
I have, or had.

35:51.233 --> 35:53.651
But now that I seem
to have that all
straightened away,

35:53.735 --> 35:56.695
I can't seem to solve
this other problem.

35:57.197 --> 36:00.407
Well, you know what
they always say, my man.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.409
No. What?

36:05.705 --> 36:08.958
"He who lives by the sword
shall die by the sword."

36:10.418 --> 36:13.379
Don't let the door hit you
in the ass on the way out.

36:15.465 --> 36:16.632
Later.

36:19.970 --> 36:23.264
DAVE: We'll have more smooth
sounds in just one minute.

36:23.765 --> 36:27.601
But first, at 10 minutes
to the hour, we're
broadcasting from KRML

36:27.686 --> 36:29.562
in the Carmel Rancho
Shopping Center,

36:29.646 --> 36:32.773
home of the Buccaneer,
the man's boutique.

36:38.446 --> 36:40.531
KRML, Dave Garver speaking.

36:40.615 --> 36:42.867
The whole point in having
an answering service

36:42.951 --> 36:46.412
is to call them
once in a while and see
if you've got any messages.

36:46.496 --> 36:48.372
Hi, Evelyn. What's happening?

36:48.540 --> 36:51.417
What could be
happening, darling?
You're not here yet.

36:51.501 --> 36:52.751
"Yet"?

36:52.836 --> 36:55.838
I hope you like
pastrami, because they
didn't have any corned beef.

36:55.922 --> 36:58.340
Now, wait a minute.
Just hold on.

36:59.134 --> 37:02.177
Are you trying to tell me
you forgot that we have
a date tonight?

37:02.262 --> 37:05.055
I thought I was supposed
to call you on that.

37:05.140 --> 37:06.974
It's just that I feel
kind of silly sitting here

37:07.058 --> 37:08.976
in my brand-new
lounging pajamas.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.937
I just assumed...

37:13.315 --> 37:15.149
Apparently, I assumed wrong.

37:15.483 --> 37:17.651
That's right.
You assumed wrong.

37:20.739 --> 37:23.908
You don't have to come over,
Dave, if you've got something
better to do.

37:23.992 --> 37:26.243
No, that's all right, I'll
be over in a little while.

37:26.328 --> 37:28.704
You and I are gonna
have to have a talk.

37:29.331 --> 37:31.290
Whatever you say.

37:31.374 --> 37:34.376
In the meantime, haven't
you forgotten something else?

37:34.461 --> 37:35.836
What's that?

37:36.379 --> 37:38.547
Weren't you gonna
play Misty for me?

37:40.175 --> 37:42.593
Yeah. I have
that one right here.

37:42.677 --> 37:44.428
Thank you, darling.

38:03.365 --> 38:07.576
And now we have
a pretty one for lonely
lovers on a cool, cool night.

38:08.078 --> 38:11.038
It's the great Erroll Garner
classic, Misty.

38:12.248 --> 38:14.375
And this one is
especially for Evelyn.

38:14.459 --> 38:15.542
(DOORBELL RINGS)

38:15.627 --> 38:17.211
EVELYN: Just a second.

38:36.398 --> 38:37.731
Come in.

38:41.736 --> 38:45.656
Hi.

38:49.327 --> 38:51.537
Cold night, huh?
Yeah.

38:51.621 --> 38:54.248
But you got here
anyway. Stout fella.

38:54.666 --> 38:56.875
Look, Evelyn, there's
something we're gonna
have to get straight.

38:56.960 --> 39:00.254
It's amazing what a man
will go through for
a hot pastrami sandwich.

39:00.338 --> 39:01.422
Now look...

39:01.506 --> 39:03.841
Wait a minute. You haven't
told me how nice I look.

39:03.925 --> 39:05.467
You look fine.

39:05.552 --> 39:07.511
The lady at the store
guaranteed you'd flip.

39:07.595 --> 39:08.846
Now, listen. Can we talk?

39:08.930 --> 39:10.180
Wait.

39:10.265 --> 39:11.515
First...

39:23.570 --> 39:24.862
Surprise.

39:26.114 --> 39:27.740
Don't you like them?

39:27.949 --> 39:29.366
Yeah, they're great, but...

39:29.451 --> 39:32.494
Don't spoil my fun, darling.
I love to give you things.

39:32.620 --> 39:34.747
It's Madame Butterfly time.

39:35.248 --> 39:39.376
First, friendly neighborhood
geisha remove honorable shoes.

39:39.461 --> 39:41.628
Stop it, Evelyn!

39:41.713 --> 39:43.589
Now, we've gotta talk!

39:44.591 --> 39:46.050
Have I done something wrong?

39:46.134 --> 39:49.136
I'm just trying to be
straight with you, that's all.

39:50.555 --> 39:52.431
Be nice to me instead.

39:52.515 --> 39:53.974
Jesus Christ!

39:57.020 --> 39:58.771
I don't understand.

40:00.106 --> 40:03.192
Are you trying to say
you don't love me anymore?

40:04.319 --> 40:06.945
I never told you
that I loved you.

40:07.030 --> 40:09.448
Not in words, maybe,

40:09.532 --> 40:12.910
but, Dave, there are lots
of ways of saying things that
have nothing to do with words.

40:12.994 --> 40:15.287
I'm sorry you
read it that way.

40:17.999 --> 40:20.000
It's that other
bitch, isn't it?

40:21.086 --> 40:22.503
What are you talking about?

40:22.587 --> 40:24.505
The picture in the
silver frame in your dresser.

40:24.589 --> 40:26.924
Look, that picture has got
nothing to do with you.

40:27.008 --> 40:29.134
What does have to do with me?

40:29.219 --> 40:30.385
I never lied to you.

40:30.470 --> 40:32.262
Big deal.
He never lied to me.

40:32.347 --> 40:35.307
What do you want for that?
The Congressional
Medal of Honor?

40:35.391 --> 40:36.850
So long.

40:36.935 --> 40:38.769
What am I supposed to do?

40:38.853 --> 40:41.105
Sit here all dressed up
in my little whore suit,

40:41.189 --> 40:43.065
waiting for my lord
and master to call?

40:43.149 --> 40:44.900
Nobody asked you
to wait for anything.

40:44.984 --> 40:46.860
You're not dumping me,
buster blue eyes.

40:46.945 --> 40:48.529
Get off my back, Evelyn!

40:48.613 --> 40:52.157
Get off your back?
That's where you've been
keeping me, isn't it?

40:52.450 --> 40:55.953
You're nothing!
You're not even good in bed!

40:56.037 --> 40:58.580
I just felt sorry
for you, that's all!

40:58.665 --> 41:02.167
Bastard! You poor,
pathetic bastard!

41:04.712 --> 41:05.963
(DOOR SLAMMING)

41:06.047 --> 41:07.840
(PHONE RINGING)

41:29.028 --> 41:30.320
Hello?
I'm sorry.

41:30.405 --> 41:32.573
I didn't mean
those things I said.

41:33.283 --> 41:34.449
Will I see you tomorrow?

41:35.535 --> 41:36.827
You don't listen, do you?

41:36.911 --> 41:40.372
Oh, let me come over.
If I could just see you,
just talk to you.

41:40.456 --> 41:41.957
No, Evelyn.

41:42.041 --> 41:44.543
But I love you, David.
I love you.

41:56.306 --> 41:58.015
(PHONE RINGING)

42:01.060 --> 42:03.937
EVELYN: David,
if I could just...

42:29.005 --> 42:31.215
TOBIE: What's the matter?

42:31.299 --> 42:33.258
DAVE: Nothing. Why?

42:33.343 --> 42:34.885
No, come on.

42:34.969 --> 42:36.970
You haven't heard one word
I've been saying to you.

42:37.055 --> 42:39.097
Yes, I have. I've heard
everything you said.

42:39.182 --> 42:41.516
You did, huh?
All right, tell me.

42:42.477 --> 42:44.353
You don't
believe me, huh?

42:44.437 --> 42:45.812
Go ahead.

42:46.814 --> 42:48.440
Okay, wise chick.

42:49.984 --> 42:52.736
We're supposed to go
to a party at Big Sur
tomorrow night,

42:52.820 --> 42:55.489
and I'm supposed to
meet you there at 9:00.

42:57.158 --> 42:59.826
And the address is...

43:02.121 --> 43:03.288
(LAUGHS)

43:03.373 --> 43:05.290
I didn't tell you that.

43:05.375 --> 43:06.792
See how you are?

43:06.876 --> 43:10.045
I don't know myself yet.
I'll call you tomorrow
about it, okay?

43:10.129 --> 43:11.421
Okay.

43:11.506 --> 43:13.048
You call me tomorrow.

43:13.716 --> 43:15.550
Honey, we better go.

43:15.635 --> 43:16.969
We're just getting
to the best part.

43:17.053 --> 43:19.846
Yeah, but I've got to
pick Anjelica up at 6:00.

43:20.890 --> 43:24.101
God! How the pain
is setting in.

43:24.185 --> 43:26.561
Come on.
She's a very nice girl.

43:26.938 --> 43:29.356
Anyway, she's
moving out tonight.

43:30.817 --> 43:33.443
Now, that's about
the best news that
I've heard in years.

43:33.528 --> 43:35.779
And Madalyn's moving in.

43:35.863 --> 43:37.072
Madalyn?

43:38.533 --> 43:39.700
(GROANS)

43:48.543 --> 43:49.960
(BANGING ON DOOR)

43:57.343 --> 43:58.427
Shit.

44:00.888 --> 44:02.431
(BANGING CONTINUES)

44:24.746 --> 44:26.246
What's going on?

44:26.331 --> 44:27.831
Don't tell me
it was asleep!

44:27.915 --> 44:29.458
What else at this
hour of the morning?

44:29.542 --> 44:31.877
Oh, I'm surprised his
conscience was that clear!

44:31.961 --> 44:33.295
What do you want, Evelyn?

44:33.379 --> 44:35.589
"What do you want, Evelyn?"
What do you want?

44:35.673 --> 44:37.007
Do I have to want something?

44:37.091 --> 44:39.676
Can't I just come over?
Or is it inconvenient?

44:39.761 --> 44:41.345
Now, wait just a...
Could it be I make a boo-boo?

44:41.429 --> 44:44.014
Could it be that
someone has been sleeping
in Papa Bear's bed?

44:44.098 --> 44:45.182
Wait a minute, God damn it!

44:45.266 --> 44:47.976
Come out, come out,
wherever you are!

44:51.481 --> 44:52.939
I thought...

44:58.237 --> 45:00.989
Oh, God, don't look
at me that way, Dave.

45:01.074 --> 45:02.949
I just don't know
what to say to you.

45:03.034 --> 45:06.495
I'm sorry I mistrusted you.
I should have known you'd
never do anything spoil it.

45:06.579 --> 45:08.080
To spoil what?

45:09.874 --> 45:10.957
What we have between us.

45:11.042 --> 45:13.001
We don't have a goddamn
thing between us.

45:13.086 --> 45:14.878
Now, how many ways
am I gonna have to
say this to you?

45:14.962 --> 45:17.464
I don't care how
many ways you say it.
It's not true!

45:17.548 --> 45:19.800
What do I have to
do to convince you?

45:19.884 --> 45:22.010
(WAILING) It's not true!

45:22.095 --> 45:24.054
It's not!

45:24.138 --> 45:25.764
What are you doing?

45:25.848 --> 45:28.517
I'm gonna get dressed and
drive you home, that's what.

45:28.601 --> 45:32.729
Why are you playing
these games? Why are you
pretending you don't love me?

45:32.814 --> 45:35.065
I don't even believe
I'm hearing this.

45:35.149 --> 45:38.151
But I love you!

45:38.236 --> 45:40.779
You haven't got the vaguest
idea what love is.

45:40.863 --> 45:43.115
We don't even know each other.

45:44.784 --> 45:46.284
Wait a minute.

45:47.620 --> 45:51.081
You don't have to do that.
I'm okay. I can drive home.

45:52.792 --> 45:54.251
Are you sure?

45:55.294 --> 45:57.045
Positive. I'm fine.

45:58.131 --> 46:00.132
Let me just wash my face, huh?

46:24.657 --> 46:26.241
(WATER RUNNING)

46:52.852 --> 46:54.060
(WATER STOPS)

47:08.743 --> 47:10.076
You ready?

47:20.421 --> 47:21.421
(KNOCKING)

47:22.215 --> 47:23.465
You okay?

47:26.677 --> 47:34.059
Evelyn?

47:42.985 --> 47:44.611
(CLATTERING)

47:47.114 --> 47:48.323
Oh, no.

47:55.831 --> 47:57.582
DAVE: How's she gonna be?

47:58.125 --> 47:59.834
Well, I sutured the wounds.

47:59.961 --> 48:01.545
It wasn't quite
as bad as it looked.

48:01.629 --> 48:03.463
It couldn't have been.

48:04.882 --> 48:08.927
You know, Dave,
I'm supposed to turn
a report in on this.

48:09.637 --> 48:12.180
But you won't.
You see, Tobie's back.

48:12.932 --> 48:14.307
I'd rather be the one
to tell her,

48:14.392 --> 48:16.309
and not have her read it
in the paper somewhere.

48:16.394 --> 48:20.564
I didn't know that.
I'll tell Marie. We'll
do the spaghetti number.

48:21.774 --> 48:23.525
Somebody gonna
be around here today?

48:23.609 --> 48:25.277
Me. I'll be here.

48:25.903 --> 48:27.737
I bombed her out
pretty good.

48:27.822 --> 48:30.282
Better let her sleep it off
before you take her home.

48:30.366 --> 48:32.158
And how long will that be?

48:32.243 --> 48:34.327
It's hard to say. Why?

48:34.412 --> 48:35.912
I'd like to take
Tobie out tonight.

48:35.997 --> 48:37.831
No problem.

48:37.915 --> 48:41.167
She'll wake up sometime
this afternoon, 5:00 or so.

48:42.878 --> 48:44.921
Is she gonna be all right?

48:46.757 --> 48:49.175
Well, the cuts were really
pretty superficial.

48:49.260 --> 48:51.678
I mean, do you think
she'll try it again?

48:53.514 --> 48:56.641
Chances are against it.
But I'd watch her.

48:57.768 --> 49:02.188
I wouldn't leave her alone
if she seems unusually
depressed or insecure.

49:02.898 --> 49:05.734
Better get some
sleep yourself.
You look like hell.

49:07.570 --> 49:08.778
FRANK: Call me if you need me.

49:08.863 --> 49:11.573
DAVE: Hey, thanks, Frank.
I really appreciate it.

49:31.385 --> 49:33.178
How are you feeling?

49:33.554 --> 49:35.930
Okay. Fine.

49:36.057 --> 49:37.182
Here.

49:41.437 --> 49:42.771
Thank you.

49:42.897 --> 49:44.898
Brought you a little soup.

49:46.942 --> 49:48.443
It looks good.

49:53.658 --> 49:55.492
I don't know what to say.

49:55.576 --> 49:58.244
It frightens me
thinking about it.

49:58.329 --> 50:00.205
Well, don't think about it.

50:00.289 --> 50:03.208
Oh, I don't mean me.
I mean you.

50:06.962 --> 50:09.923
"Girl commits suicide
in disc jockey's home."

50:10.716 --> 50:14.469
It's not very good publicity
for a man in your position.

50:16.764 --> 50:20.141
Get some rest.
As soon as you feel better,
I'll take you home.

50:20.309 --> 50:21.935
Thank you, David.

50:22.603 --> 50:24.688
(PHONE RINGING)

50:26.065 --> 50:28.525
I got your clothes hung up
in the closet there.

50:28.609 --> 50:31.069
Maybe you better
answer the phone.

50:33.197 --> 50:35.782
Yeah. I'll get it
in the other room.

50:45.376 --> 50:46.543
Hello.

50:46.711 --> 50:50.547
Hi. Hey I just
wanted to check.
We still on for tonight?

50:50.631 --> 50:53.883
Yeah, I'm all dressed
and ready to go.
What time is the party?

50:53.968 --> 50:58.888
Well, Madalyn's already
left, and she won't be
back for a long time,

50:58.973 --> 51:01.182
and I was just thinking...

51:01.642 --> 51:02.976
Would you be
terribly disappointed

51:03.060 --> 51:06.229
if we didn't go to
the party and just
stayed here instead?

51:07.565 --> 51:09.858
Well, I think I can
bear up under it.

51:11.819 --> 51:13.486
Don't be too long.

51:13.571 --> 51:15.155
That's me at the door.

51:15.239 --> 51:16.823
David,

51:16.907 --> 51:20.910
the way I look at it,
the hell with Sausalito.

51:23.164 --> 51:24.414
Bye-bye.

51:27.918 --> 51:29.961
(EVELYN BREATHING HEAVILY)

51:45.895 --> 51:47.479
(PANTING)

51:56.238 --> 51:57.280
No.

51:57.364 --> 51:58.531
Evelyn?

51:58.616 --> 51:59.908
(SCREAMING)

51:59.992 --> 52:01.284
What's the matter?
Take it easy.

52:01.368 --> 52:02.660
I had a dream.

52:02.745 --> 52:06.998
I was drowning in the ocean
and I called to you,
but you just stood there

52:07.082 --> 52:09.000
watching. Watching.

52:11.212 --> 52:12.879
It was just a dream.

52:12.963 --> 52:14.839
Oh, God, I'm so alone.

52:15.758 --> 52:17.008
Hold me.

52:17.968 --> 52:21.387
Hold me, Dave. Please. Please.

52:21.722 --> 52:24.015
Yeah. Yeah.

52:25.100 --> 52:28.520
Tighter.

52:30.189 --> 52:34.692
Don't let me go.

53:54.440 --> 53:55.607
David!

53:59.528 --> 54:01.654
I woke up and you were gone.

54:06.493 --> 54:07.619
(HANGS UP PHONE)

54:08.787 --> 54:12.582
If you have something
planned for tonight,
you could just take me home.

54:14.126 --> 54:15.919
Maybe that'd be best.

54:19.340 --> 54:21.299
No, no, there's nothing.

54:22.217 --> 54:23.343
Good.

54:29.016 --> 54:30.892
Isn't this nice?

54:30.976 --> 54:32.852
Just us here, together.

54:50.996 --> 54:52.622
Here we go again.

54:55.960 --> 54:58.211
Stone-cold dead in the market.

55:00.464 --> 55:02.757
Must have been quite a party.

55:04.885 --> 55:06.469
Go away, Birdie.

55:07.054 --> 55:10.348
Any other bodies,
any other juiceheads
around here?

55:12.393 --> 55:15.561
Come back tomorrow, will you?
Or next year sometime.

55:15.646 --> 55:17.855
I better check the workbench.

55:24.071 --> 55:26.406
All right,
break it up in here.

55:26.991 --> 55:29.701
Looks like old times
around this place.

55:30.369 --> 55:37.583
Evelyn?

55:37.668 --> 55:39.544
Lose something, tiger?

55:39.878 --> 55:42.088
Look, Birdie, you
couldn't find it
within your heart

55:42.172 --> 55:44.173
to come back
at a later time,
could you?

55:44.258 --> 55:46.426
This is a later
time, pussycat.

55:46.552 --> 55:49.220
I'm paying you back
for the day I blew last week.

55:49.304 --> 55:54.017
Evelyn?

55:54.935 --> 55:57.270
Very funny, Birdie.
Very funny.

55:57.813 --> 56:02.108
What I can't figure out
is, with all this kind
of action going on in here,

56:02.192 --> 56:04.736
what are you doing
out there couching it?

56:04.820 --> 56:06.779
What is this, some
kind of Kinsey Report?

56:06.864 --> 56:09.741
Do I come over
to your house and ask
a lot of dumb questions?

56:09.825 --> 56:11.367
Well, you just
ought to, pussycat.

56:11.452 --> 56:14.412
Might open up a whole
new way of life to you.

56:14.788 --> 56:16.247
(PHONE RINGING)

56:16.331 --> 56:17.540
Hold it.

56:17.624 --> 56:20.501
Let's try to show
a little class, shall we?

56:23.172 --> 56:25.089
Mr. Garver's residence.

56:27.760 --> 56:29.010
Oh, I'll see.

56:29.428 --> 56:32.138
Do you want to talk
to a Madge Brenner?

56:32.222 --> 56:34.348
Yeah. I want to talk to her.

56:34.433 --> 56:35.683
Thanks. Hello.

56:36.185 --> 56:39.228
Hello, Mr. Garver?
Madge Brenner.

56:39.313 --> 56:42.482
We like the tape
on your show.
Like it very much.

56:42.649 --> 56:45.735
There are one or two others
still in the running,
but frankly...

56:45.819 --> 56:47.195
Why can't we have lunch today?

56:47.279 --> 56:48.488
Windjammer still good?

56:48.572 --> 56:49.947
Yeah, still very good.

56:50.032 --> 56:53.159
Reserve a table in your name.
See you then, Mr. Garver.

56:53.619 --> 56:55.203
Great. Bye-bye.

56:56.205 --> 56:58.331
Looks like we found Evelyn.

57:01.627 --> 57:04.295
"Good morning, darling.
Gone shopping.

57:04.379 --> 57:06.672
"Back in a flash
with the hash."

57:06.757 --> 57:09.175
Ooh! A little humor in there.

57:09.259 --> 57:11.886
"Love and kisses, Evelyn."

57:11.970 --> 57:13.638
And then it says,

57:13.722 --> 57:16.557
"If you can't find
your keys, don't worry.

57:18.727 --> 57:20.603
"I borrowed your car."

57:27.820 --> 57:30.279
Here's your key,
and here's your copy.

57:30.364 --> 57:32.365
That'll be 40 cents, please.

57:38.413 --> 57:40.540
Thank you. Have a nice day.

58:16.743 --> 58:19.537
David?
I stopped by my...

58:21.874 --> 58:22.832
Hi.

58:22.916 --> 58:25.126
Don't you look all gussied up?

58:25.752 --> 58:29.922
Well, good. I was gonna
cook brunch, but this calls
for something more festive.

58:30.048 --> 58:32.425
How about the Marquis?
My treat.

58:32.801 --> 58:34.218
After all I put you through,
it's the least...

58:34.303 --> 58:36.345
No, no. I have a lunch date.
Business.

58:36.430 --> 58:37.346
Business?

58:37.431 --> 58:39.807
Yeah. Can I have
my car keys?

58:39.892 --> 58:41.058
Sure.

58:41.143 --> 58:43.436
I think you ought to
take it easy, anyway.
Get some rest.

58:43.520 --> 58:47.064
Yeah, I do feel
a little tired.

58:50.944 --> 58:52.236
(DOOR CLOSING)

58:58.994 --> 59:00.411
(MADGE LAUGHING)

59:00.495 --> 59:01.787
Very funny, Dave.

59:02.497 --> 59:05.750
Now, let's talk show.
Tell me, what do you
think of the concept?

59:05.834 --> 59:08.044
The unstructured,

59:08.128 --> 59:12.298
the loosey-goosey,
Monterey pop,
Woodstock kind of thing?

59:12.883 --> 59:16.135
I like it.
I like it very much, and
I think I can handle it.

59:16.428 --> 59:18.221
So do I.

59:18.305 --> 59:21.390
I'll keep this to promote
your new career with.

59:22.517 --> 59:25.478
You'll be working with kids,
bright and marvelous.

59:25.562 --> 59:27.396
But they take handling.

59:27.481 --> 59:29.398
You know, if this show
goes the way I think
it's going to,

59:29.483 --> 59:30.733
there's no reason
in the world why...

59:30.817 --> 59:33.194
Well, isn't this cozy?

59:33.278 --> 59:35.196
So this is your
business lunch?

59:35.280 --> 59:37.114
How's business?

59:37.950 --> 59:39.992
Friend of yours?
Just another trick, honey.

59:40.077 --> 59:41.118
That's enough.

59:41.203 --> 59:42.995
Is that your idea of a dish?

59:43.080 --> 59:45.414
My God, she's a little
old for you, isn't she?

59:45.499 --> 59:47.792
What is this,
"Be Kind to Senior
Citizens Week"?

59:47.876 --> 59:49.001
Get out of here!

59:49.086 --> 59:50.419
It's not that I mind
you being a bastard,

59:50.504 --> 59:52.922
but do you have to be
such a tasteless bastard?

59:53.006 --> 59:57.301
Stop it, you son of
a bitch! She couldn't
get laid in a lumber camp!

59:57.386 --> 01:00:00.721
Stop it, you son of a bitch!
You're hurting me!

01:00:00.806 --> 01:00:03.474
Stop it, you dirty
bastard! Oh, no!

01:00:03.558 --> 01:00:06.352
Stop it! Dave!

01:00:06.436 --> 01:00:09.230
Oh, no! No! No! No!

01:00:09.314 --> 01:00:12.358
No! Don't leave me!
Don't leave me!

01:00:12.442 --> 01:00:16.529
She's nothing!
Nothing! Nothing!

01:00:19.199 --> 01:00:20.283
I love you!

01:00:20.367 --> 01:00:21.492
Get her out of here, man.

01:00:21.576 --> 01:00:22.910
DRIVER: Where to?

01:00:23.203 --> 01:00:25.705
I did it because I love you.
Don't you understand that?

01:00:25.789 --> 01:00:26.831
I love you!

01:00:26.915 --> 01:00:28.582
Where to, mister?
Move!

01:00:28.667 --> 01:00:31.294
It's because I love you!
Dave, please.

01:01:10.208 --> 01:01:11.584
This is a private beach.

01:01:11.668 --> 01:01:13.127
I want to talk to you.

01:01:13.211 --> 01:01:15.338
I don't want to talk to you.

01:01:21.762 --> 01:01:23.512
Are you drunk?

01:01:23.597 --> 01:01:25.848
No, but that's
not a bad idea.

01:01:26.641 --> 01:01:28.267
Why, David?

01:01:28.352 --> 01:01:29.560
Why what? Drunk?

01:01:29.644 --> 01:01:31.645
No. Why last night?

01:01:33.273 --> 01:01:35.900
That's what I came
to explain to you.

01:01:36.693 --> 01:01:38.069
Okay, good.

01:01:38.612 --> 01:01:42.573
But I think we should
understand each other.
I'm not very happy with you.

01:01:42.699 --> 01:01:43.991
Well, that's fair
enough, Tobie.

01:01:44.076 --> 01:01:46.452
Whatever it was,
you could have called me.

01:01:46.536 --> 01:01:48.579
No, I couldn't.

01:01:48.663 --> 01:01:49.914
Why not?

01:01:53.960 --> 01:01:56.837
I couldn't tell you
the truth last night.

01:01:56.922 --> 01:01:59.298
I'm not gonna lie
to you anymore.

01:02:02.344 --> 01:02:04.762
Now, why do you
have to say that?

01:02:13.730 --> 01:02:17.066
I just didn't
want to take a chance
she'd try it again.

01:02:17.150 --> 01:02:18.818
What if she does?

01:02:20.737 --> 01:02:23.406
Well, I swear to you,
if she ever tries it,

01:02:23.490 --> 01:02:26.117
I'd just let her
go right on ahead.

01:02:32.707 --> 01:02:33.791
Oh, God!

01:02:37.129 --> 01:02:39.839
Oh, my God.

01:02:45.554 --> 01:02:47.179
What in the...

01:03:10.078 --> 01:03:12.121
(EVELYN PANTING)

01:03:23.550 --> 01:03:24.967
(GRUNTING)

01:03:38.773 --> 01:03:39.940
(PANTING)

01:03:40.192 --> 01:03:43.152
(FABRIC TEARING)

01:03:47.866 --> 01:03:52.495
(SCREAMING)

01:03:55.081 --> 01:03:57.333
Oh, God, help me!

01:03:57.417 --> 01:03:59.752
Please, somebody, help me!

01:04:05.050 --> 01:04:07.384
Help me, somebody!

01:04:07.469 --> 01:04:09.887
Oh, God, help me!

01:04:31.076 --> 01:04:32.201
Stay back, buddy.

01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:33.953
I live here, man.

01:04:40.669 --> 01:04:43.379
Is she your
housecleaning lady, Garver?

01:04:45.674 --> 01:04:47.967
Okay, boys,
let's take her out.

01:04:50.303 --> 01:04:51.887
Watch your step.

01:04:51.972 --> 01:04:52.972
Birdie.

01:04:55.308 --> 01:04:58.769
It's gonna cost you double
to clean up this mess.

01:04:59.938 --> 01:05:01.522
MAN: Watch your step.

01:05:01.606 --> 01:05:03.315
Dave Garver?

01:05:03.400 --> 01:05:04.525
Yeah.

01:05:04.609 --> 01:05:06.277
I'm Sergeant McCallum.

01:05:09.114 --> 01:05:11.865
Any ideas?

01:05:11.950 --> 01:05:13.993
About what?

01:05:14.077 --> 01:05:16.370
About your
girlfriend in there.

01:05:18.498 --> 01:05:20.624
Hey, that's not my girlfriend.

01:05:20.709 --> 01:05:23.460
Let me get that straight
right in front.

01:05:24.462 --> 01:05:25.713
(GATE CLOSING)

01:05:25.797 --> 01:05:27.881
(AMBULANCE DEPARTS)

01:05:38.351 --> 01:05:41.395
More or less a casual
acquaintance, you'd say?

01:05:41.479 --> 01:05:43.147
That's right.

01:05:43.231 --> 01:05:45.608
She just dropped by
to hack up your wardrobe
and your cleaning lady?

01:05:45.692 --> 01:05:47.860
Is that what you're
trying to tell me?

01:05:49.988 --> 01:05:52.448
I'm not trying to tell you
anything, Sergeant.

01:05:52.532 --> 01:05:55.993
Well then, maybe
you ought to. The lady
almost got herself killed.

01:05:56.077 --> 01:06:00.080
And I'm stumbling
around in my stupid way
trying to find out why.

01:06:01.374 --> 01:06:03.042
What'll you have?

01:06:03.543 --> 01:06:05.419
This Evelyn Draper,
where does she come from?

01:06:06.254 --> 01:06:09.173
I don't know.
What about her family?

01:06:09.257 --> 01:06:11.258
I don't know that either.

01:06:12.802 --> 01:06:17.056
She just listens
to my radio show, and
we met one night. That's all.

01:06:17.641 --> 01:06:18.974
Practically a stranger.

01:06:19.059 --> 01:06:20.184
That's right.

01:06:20.268 --> 01:06:23.062
Then how does she
happen to have a key
to your front door?

01:06:24.272 --> 01:06:25.981
I don't know that either.

01:06:26.107 --> 01:06:29.652
It boils down to,
you don't know
a hell of a lot, do you?

01:06:29.736 --> 01:06:32.905
What it boils down to is
I'm getting sick of
your questions.

01:06:32.989 --> 01:06:34.657
And so am I!

01:06:34.741 --> 01:06:37.493
But they get upset
with me down at the store
if I don't ask them.

01:06:38.703 --> 01:06:40.871
Just take her through.
I'll be right along.

01:06:40.955 --> 01:06:42.122
Right.

01:06:42.207 --> 01:06:43.791
Take her through what?

01:06:43.875 --> 01:06:45.084
Booking.

01:06:48.046 --> 01:06:50.881
What she really needs
is psychiatric help.

01:06:51.925 --> 01:06:53.133
Really?

01:06:56.054 --> 01:06:59.098
Now, look, those cuts
on her wrists...

01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:02.935
Don't know
anything about those.

01:07:07.607 --> 01:07:09.566
There's one other thing.

01:07:10.360 --> 01:07:12.444
I know. "Don't leave town."

01:07:12.862 --> 01:07:16.198
I was gonna say,
"Why don't you play
some Mantovani sometime?"

01:07:18.743 --> 01:07:20.619
Didn't know you
liked the show, Sergeant.

01:07:20.704 --> 01:07:22.788
I don't. I like Mantovani.

01:13:20.188 --> 01:13:21.813
(PLAYING UPBEAT JAZZ)

01:14:11.030 --> 01:14:12.531
MAN: Go ahead, play!

01:14:25.837 --> 01:14:27.170
MAN: Whoo!

01:14:27.255 --> 01:14:30.048
ANNOUNCER: Those of you
who may have played brass
instruments in high school,

01:14:30.133 --> 01:14:32.801
you know that was
triple-tonguing, baby.

01:14:32.885 --> 01:14:34.511
Let's give his tongue
a nice hand!

01:14:34.595 --> 01:14:36.096
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:14:36.180 --> 01:14:38.890
He might just be
the fastest tongue
in the West!

01:14:41.352 --> 01:14:42.519
Come on.

01:14:42.603 --> 01:14:44.646
All right, I'm coming.

01:14:46.315 --> 01:14:48.066
(PLAYING UPBEAT JAZZ)

01:16:01.807 --> 01:16:03.767
What do you say...

01:16:04.393 --> 01:16:05.477
How about
something to eat?

01:16:05.561 --> 01:16:07.687
I've got to pick up
my roommate, Annabel.

01:16:07.772 --> 01:16:09.231
Madalyn's your roommate.

01:16:09.315 --> 01:16:11.233
I found my man,
and I'm moving out.

01:16:11.317 --> 01:16:13.026
And Annabel's moving in.

01:16:13.110 --> 01:16:14.277
Right.

01:16:14.820 --> 01:16:15.987
Ciao.

01:16:17.990 --> 01:16:18.990
Later.

01:16:50.898 --> 01:16:52.107
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

01:16:52.191 --> 01:16:54.651
MAN: Thank you.
Thank you very kindly.

01:16:59.031 --> 01:17:00.323
(PLAYING SMOOTH JAZZ)

01:18:01.886 --> 01:18:03.261
That was the Cannonball
Adderley Group.

01:18:03.346 --> 01:18:05.680
And they're making it
happen out at the Monterey
Jazz Festival,

01:18:05.765 --> 01:18:09.559
along with Duke Ellington,
Woody Herman, Joe Williams
and many others.

01:18:09.643 --> 01:18:11.186
Still got tickets
for Sunday night.

01:18:11.270 --> 01:18:14.898
So get on out there
because that's where
it's happening.

01:18:14.982 --> 01:18:19.402
Now we're gonna hear
from the Gator Creek
Organization and Feelin' Fine.

01:18:25.034 --> 01:18:26.868
KRML. Dave Garver.

01:18:29.080 --> 01:18:30.246
Hello?

01:18:30.956 --> 01:18:32.665
EVELYN: Play Misty for me.

01:18:37.088 --> 01:18:38.254
David?

01:18:39.256 --> 01:18:42.300
I didn't mean to
shake you up. I'm sorry.

01:18:42.385 --> 01:18:44.761
Pretty stupid of me.

01:18:44.845 --> 01:18:46.721
I've been released.

01:18:46.806 --> 01:18:49.766
Therapy. It was a bad dream,
but it's over.

01:18:50.226 --> 01:18:51.601
Where are you?

01:18:51.685 --> 01:18:53.853
The airport. San Francisco.

01:18:53.938 --> 01:18:57.399
I've only got a minute
or two between planes.
Got a job in Hawaii.

01:18:57.483 --> 01:18:59.359
You're all right, then?

01:18:59.485 --> 01:19:01.236
Fine, David. Fine.

01:19:02.780 --> 01:19:06.074
I just want to say
how sorry I am
about everything.

01:19:06.158 --> 01:19:07.617
Forget it. I have.

01:19:07.701 --> 01:19:09.035
I hope so.

01:19:09.620 --> 01:19:12.038
"Because this maiden
she lived with
no other thought"

01:19:12.123 --> 01:19:14.624
"Than to love and
be loved by you"

01:19:17.545 --> 01:19:19.504
Are you near a radio?

01:19:19.588 --> 01:19:21.297
No.

01:19:21.382 --> 01:19:23.425
But play it for me anyway.

01:20:21.817 --> 01:20:23.902
(SCREAMING)

01:21:15.538 --> 01:21:17.622
(PHONE RINGING)

01:21:37.309 --> 01:21:38.935
Hello.
McCALLUM: Garver?

01:21:39.019 --> 01:21:40.562
Yeah.
Sergeant McCallum.

01:21:40.646 --> 01:21:42.480
Sorry to wake you,
but something's come up.

01:21:42.565 --> 01:21:46.401
Yeah, I know.
She just paid me a visit
with a butcher knife.

01:21:46.485 --> 01:21:50.697
Why? Because she was
released on parole pending
further legal action.

01:21:51.323 --> 01:21:52.407
When?

01:21:54.702 --> 01:21:56.035
A week ago.

01:21:56.120 --> 01:21:58.955
Well, I sure like the way
you broke your ass to
let me know about it.

01:21:59.039 --> 01:22:00.540
I just found out
about it myself.

01:22:00.624 --> 01:22:03.042
Who's in charge
down there, anyway?

01:22:04.044 --> 01:22:06.212
Now, look. Do you
want to help find her

01:22:06.297 --> 01:22:08.756
or would you rather just
sit there and bellyache?

01:22:09.842 --> 01:22:11.092
All right.

01:22:11.176 --> 01:22:12.260
Good.

01:22:12.761 --> 01:22:15.305
Now, exactly what
did she say to you?

01:22:15.806 --> 01:22:19.684
I told you. She said that
she was well and that
she was going to Hawaii.

01:22:20.185 --> 01:22:21.519
What else?

01:22:22.688 --> 01:22:23.730
I already told you.

01:22:23.814 --> 01:22:25.315
Tell me again.

01:22:25.441 --> 01:22:27.942
You know, Sergeant,
you really make
lousy conversation.

01:22:28.027 --> 01:22:31.446
You make lousy coffee.
Come on, what else
did she say?

01:22:32.323 --> 01:22:34.115
Nothing, except...

01:22:34.199 --> 01:22:35.658
Except what?

01:22:35.743 --> 01:22:38.661
It was nothing.
It was a line from a poem.

01:22:39.038 --> 01:22:40.163
What poem?

01:22:40.247 --> 01:22:42.248
If I knew that, I'd know
the line. Wouldn't I?

01:22:42.333 --> 01:22:44.208
Try to remember.

01:22:44.293 --> 01:22:46.169
You know, McCallum,
it's getting late.

01:22:46.253 --> 01:22:47.795
You're sounding
very monotonous.

01:22:47.880 --> 01:22:51.257
Well, now, you're
not exactly my idea
of a swinging date either.

01:22:51.342 --> 01:22:53.134
Good night, McCallum.

01:22:55.054 --> 01:22:58.348
Hey, what happened
to the Mantovani?

01:22:58.474 --> 01:22:59.766
The what?

01:22:59.850 --> 01:23:04.979
Well, I heard the show,
but I never did hear
you play Mantovani.

01:23:05.064 --> 01:23:07.398
You really did
listen to the show.

01:23:07.483 --> 01:23:10.151
Friend, if we had a TV
down at the station,

01:23:10.235 --> 01:23:12.945
I'd break my arm
before I turned your show on.

01:23:13.072 --> 01:23:14.530
Thanks a lot.

01:23:16.742 --> 01:23:20.411
Just hope we're lucky enough
to grab her the next time
she tries it.

01:23:20.496 --> 01:23:22.538
Tries what?

01:23:22.623 --> 01:23:24.582
To kill you.

01:23:24.667 --> 01:23:27.752
Yeah. And if you're
not lucky enough...

01:23:27.836 --> 01:23:29.379
That'd be hell.

01:23:30.089 --> 01:23:34.050
The guys down at the station
would have to chip in and
buy a TV.

01:23:34.385 --> 01:23:36.678
You're a great
comfort, Sergeant.

01:23:36.762 --> 01:23:38.805
You will change the locks?

01:24:09.128 --> 01:24:10.169
Hi.

01:24:10.629 --> 01:24:15.258
Nothing like a nice brisk
walk in the woods to put
roses on a girl's cheeks.

01:24:16.218 --> 01:24:17.635
How are you?

01:24:18.762 --> 01:24:20.471
Not so good, honey.

01:24:24.768 --> 01:24:26.060
She's back.

01:24:26.145 --> 01:24:27.228
Who?

01:24:29.481 --> 01:24:32.650
Evelyn Draper, the girl
who tried to kill Birdie.

01:24:32.776 --> 01:24:35.361
How can... How can
she be back?

01:24:35.446 --> 01:24:38.322
I thought they'd put her
in a state sanitarium.

01:24:39.158 --> 01:24:41.117
They did, but
they let her out.

01:24:42.077 --> 01:24:44.370
Does that mean
she's all right?

01:24:44.997 --> 01:24:46.497
Theoretically.

01:24:49.501 --> 01:24:50.793
(SIGHS)

01:24:50.878 --> 01:24:52.503
What happens now?

01:24:56.133 --> 01:25:00.386
I think you and I ought to
stay away from each other
for a couple of days,

01:25:00.596 --> 01:25:03.306
just in case she's
tagging after me.

01:25:05.726 --> 01:25:08.019
She's already following you,
isn't she?

01:25:08.520 --> 01:25:11.189
I don't want you
to worry about it.
I can handle myself.

01:25:11.273 --> 01:25:13.191
Yeah. So could Birdie.

01:25:30.292 --> 01:25:32.502
All right then, you stand by.

01:25:36.298 --> 01:25:38.716
Well, they're all set
to trace the call.

01:25:39.218 --> 01:25:42.595
Now, when she phones you,
just mention her by name
right away, Evelyn,

01:25:42.679 --> 01:25:44.514
and they start to trace her.

01:25:44.640 --> 01:25:48.100
All you gotta do after that
is just keep her talking.

01:25:54.024 --> 01:25:56.818
Fifteen minutes before
the hour here at KRML

01:25:56.902 --> 01:25:59.237
and here's It's Not Unusual.

01:26:05.410 --> 01:26:07.537
I guess it hasn't
come to you yet, huh?

01:26:07.621 --> 01:26:09.247
What?

01:26:09.414 --> 01:26:10.790
What she said.

01:26:10.874 --> 01:26:14.001
Over the phone last night?
Part of a poem or something.

01:26:14.086 --> 01:26:15.711
You told me were
gonna try to remember.

01:26:15.796 --> 01:26:20.049
I thought I had that,
but I've forgotten.
Is it that important?

01:26:20.133 --> 01:26:23.094
Until we pick her up,
everything's important.

01:26:24.930 --> 01:26:26.597
(SIGHS)

01:26:28.100 --> 01:26:29.600
What's wrong?

01:26:30.227 --> 01:26:32.770
I'm worried
about my girlfriend
with all this going on.

01:26:32.855 --> 01:26:35.398
They're so damn
isolated down there.

01:26:36.024 --> 01:26:39.735
I'm thinking the best thing
to do is just call Al Monte
and have him sub for me.

01:26:39.820 --> 01:26:43.239
Now, look. The only chance
we've got is when she
phones in here tonight.

01:26:43.323 --> 01:26:45.241
You've got to be here,
right on that mike.

01:26:45.325 --> 01:26:46.325
If she phones.

01:26:46.410 --> 01:26:48.286
She will. Believe me.

01:26:49.204 --> 01:26:51.163
But only if you're here.

01:26:53.584 --> 01:26:55.042
I'll tell you what I'll do.

01:26:55.127 --> 01:26:56.752
If it'll make you
feel any better,

01:26:56.837 --> 01:27:00.131
I'll go over and check
your girlfriend's house
myself, okay?

01:27:00.799 --> 01:27:02.800
I'd sure appreciate that.

01:27:04.052 --> 01:27:06.512
She lives on the Highlands
on Spindrift Road.

01:27:06.597 --> 01:27:08.139
I think it's the fourth
or fifth house down.

01:27:08.223 --> 01:27:10.349
"Williams" is on the mailbox.

01:27:10.434 --> 01:27:11.559
Why don't you phone her?

01:27:11.643 --> 01:27:12.727
Okay.

01:27:12.811 --> 01:27:14.353
Tell her to be expecting me.

01:27:14.438 --> 01:27:15.688
McCallum.

01:27:17.107 --> 01:27:18.691
Thanks, huh?

01:27:18.775 --> 01:27:20.484
Public servant.

01:27:29.536 --> 01:27:30.912
(PHONE RINGING)

01:27:31.580 --> 01:27:32.580
Hello?

01:27:32.706 --> 01:27:35.458
Hi. I'm just checking in.
You all right?

01:27:35.542 --> 01:27:36.876
Marvelous.

01:27:37.252 --> 01:27:41.213
I'm just getting ready
to do my nails and
I got your program on.

01:27:41.924 --> 01:27:45.301
And Annabel's in
the kitchen making
a couple of coffee grogs.

01:27:45.385 --> 01:27:47.345
What more could
a girl ask for?

01:27:47.429 --> 01:27:49.513
No, honey, really
everything's fine.

01:27:49.598 --> 01:27:53.351
There's a Sergeant McCallum
that's gonna drop by
for a second,

01:27:53.435 --> 01:27:57.396
just to see if you've buttoned
up all right. Let him in,
but nobody else. Okay?

01:27:57.564 --> 01:27:58.648
Okay.

01:27:58.732 --> 01:28:03.402
Hey, David, you want
to play something soft
and dreamy for us?

01:28:04.529 --> 01:28:06.322
You got it. Bye-bye.

01:28:07.282 --> 01:28:08.658
Bye, hon.

01:28:13.246 --> 01:28:15.414
Hey, Annabel, how's
that stuff coming?

01:28:15.499 --> 01:28:17.416
DAVE ON RADIO:
Now here's something
soft and sentimental

01:28:17.501 --> 01:28:20.211
for Tobie and Annabel.

01:28:23.715 --> 01:28:26.300
Hope you like
cinnamon in yours.

01:28:26.385 --> 01:28:28.010
Whatever's right.

01:28:37.187 --> 01:28:38.396
Annabel.

01:28:52.661 --> 01:28:53.828
Good, huh?

01:28:53.912 --> 01:28:55.162
Mmm. Too much.

01:29:01.169 --> 01:29:03.004
So is this.

01:29:03.088 --> 01:29:04.922
Thank you.

01:29:05.007 --> 01:29:07.633
Just one thing.
Do you mind?

01:29:07.718 --> 01:29:09.301
No, be my guest.

01:29:10.595 --> 01:29:12.304
The eyes are wrong.

01:29:15.517 --> 01:29:17.852
David's are more...

01:29:17.936 --> 01:29:20.563
How shall I say?

01:29:20.647 --> 01:29:22.064
Colder.

01:29:22.941 --> 01:29:25.026
I didn't know you knew David.

01:29:25.152 --> 01:29:27.611
Hmm?
I didn't realize
you and David were...

01:29:30.782 --> 01:29:32.700
Were friends.

01:29:32.784 --> 01:29:34.035
Friends?

01:29:37.622 --> 01:29:40.875
(LAUGHS) Oh.
No, not friends.

01:29:44.963 --> 01:29:46.338
Not friends.

01:30:01.646 --> 01:30:03.314
God, you're dumb.

01:30:41.686 --> 01:30:44.063
EVELYN: "Because this
maiden she lived with
no other thought

01:30:44.147 --> 01:30:46.690
"Than to love and
be loved by you"

01:30:57.869 --> 01:30:59.203
(DIALING)

01:31:06.461 --> 01:31:07.711
Tobie?

01:31:08.004 --> 01:31:10.214
EVELYN: We're waiting
for you, David.

01:31:36.366 --> 01:31:39.243
(ON TAPE) This is Dave Garver
with a little verse,

01:31:39.369 --> 01:31:41.912
a little talk and
five hours of music

01:31:41.997 --> 01:31:44.915
to be very, very nice
to each other by.

01:31:45.458 --> 01:31:47.459
(GRUNTING)

01:32:29.294 --> 01:32:36.425
Careful.

01:32:37.636 --> 01:32:39.637
I might put your eye out.

01:32:46.019 --> 01:32:48.312
I'll bet David
loves your eyes.

01:33:02.702 --> 01:33:04.203
And your hair.

01:33:11.836 --> 01:33:14.672
Does he run his fingers
through your hair?

01:33:25.183 --> 01:33:27.685
Have to get you
all nice for David.

01:33:30.855 --> 01:33:32.189
For David.

01:33:42.534 --> 01:33:45.911
I hope he likes what he sees
when he walks in here,

01:33:46.871 --> 01:33:50.165
because that's what he's
taking to hell with him.

01:34:36.546 --> 01:34:38.797
(GATE CREAKING)

01:34:53.438 --> 01:34:54.938
Miss Williams?

01:35:28.473 --> 01:35:30.099
(SCREAMING)

01:35:30.183 --> 01:35:32.643
(GASPING)

01:36:33.788 --> 01:36:35.038
McCallum?

01:37:35.892 --> 01:37:37.184
(GLASS CRUNCHING)

01:38:30.655 --> 01:38:32.155
(MOANING)

01:38:33.533 --> 01:38:34.908
(MUFFLED SPEECH)

01:38:45.503 --> 01:38:47.337
(SCREAMING)

01:38:48.006 --> 01:39:32.424
(GRUNTING)

01:39:42.685 --> 01:39:44.227
(SCREAMING)

01:40:47.375 --> 01:40:52.796
DAVE ON RADIO: And now here's
a pretty one for lonely
lovers on a cool, cool night.

01:40:52.922 --> 01:40:55.841
It's the great Erroll Garner
classic, Misty.

01:40:56.300 --> 01:40:58.969
And this one is
especially for Evelyn.
